Kirk,

	Using the IP source address for authentication of remote
logins, etc. is a dangerous practice, despite its growing use.  It
is far too easy to spoof IP addresses in the internet, especially if
the source host is beyond a gateway or on an Ethernet.  I'd recommend
against relying on this sort of procedure, especially when one adds
required trust in name servers as part of the authentication path.

Steve
